132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1781
H.P. 1192 House of Representatives, April 24, 2025
An Act to Exempt from the Gasoline Tax Act Ethanol-free Gasoline
Used by Vehicles Off-road
Reference to the Committee on Taxation suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative ARDELL of Monticello.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §2903, sub-§4, ¶E, as enacted by PL 1997, c. 738, §4, is
3 amended to read:
4 E. Brought into this State in the fuel tanks of an aircraft; or
5 Sec. 2. 36 MRSA §2903, sub-§4, ¶F, as enacted by PL 1997, c. 738, §4, is
6 amended to read:
7 F. On which the collection of the tax imposed by this section is precluded by federal
8 law or regulation.; or
9 Sec. 3. 36 MRSA §2903, sub-§4, ¶G is enacted to read:
10 G. That does not contain any ethanol and is purchased for use by vehicles that are used
11 exclusively off-road.
12 Sec. 4. Documentation needed for exemption for ethanol-free fuel
13 purchased for off-road use. The State Tax Assessor shall adopt rules to determine the
14 documentation needed to implement the exemption from the Gasoline Tax Act provided in
15 the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 36, section 2903, subsection 4, paragraph G for a person
16 eligible for the exemption. Rules adopted pursuant to this section are routine technical
17 rules pursuant to Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This bill provides an exemption from the tax imposed on gasoline for internal
2200 combustion engine fuel that does not contain any ethanol and is purchased and used by
2211 vehicles when those vehicles are only used off-road.
